22%2C%20the%20thinking%20was%20that%20higher%20borrowing%20costs%20would%20put%20a%20lid%20on%20prices%2C%20which%20had%20spiraled%20endlessly%20upward%20since%20the%20pandemic%20sparked%20a%20buying%20frenzy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20didn't%20quite%20happen%2C%20and%20home%20prices%20have%20kept%20climbing%2C%20so%20much%20so%20that%20a%20recent%20report%20from%20Zillow%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-market-affordability-homebuyer-earnings-income-price-trends-covid-comparison-2024-2%5C%22%3Ewould-be%20buyers%20need%20to%20earn%2080%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20more%20than%20pre-pandemic%20to%20afford%20the%20median-priced%20home.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there's%20an%20under-the-radar%20factor%20that%20could%20soon%20pull%20down%20home%20prices%20nationally%2C%20real%20estate%20experts%20told%20Business%20Insider%20%E2%80%94%20soaring%20home%20insurance%20costs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHome%20insurance%20premiums%2C%20which%20surged%204.5%25%20year-over-year%20in%20March%20alone%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffred.stlouisfed.org%2Fseries%2FCUUR0000SEHD%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20the%20FRED%20economic%20data%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20could%20be%20the%20last%20straw%20for%20home%20buyers%20amid%20a%20litany%20of%20rising%20costs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInsurance%20comparison%20platform%20Insurify%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finsurify.com%2Fhomeowners-insurance%2Freport%2Fhome-insurance-price-projections%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20in%20a%20recent%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20annual%20insurance%20rates%20skyrocketed%2019.8%25%20from%202021%20to%202023%2C%20and%20the%20company%20forecasts%20another%206%25%20surge%20in%202024%2C%20which%20would%20push%20the%20average%20annual%20rate%20to%20%242%2C522%20by%20year-end.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReal%20estate%20experts%20said%20that%20though%20they%20aren't%20the%20top%20driver%20of%20home%20prices%20compared%20to%20mortgage%20rates%20or%20housing%20inventory%2C%20they%20still%20have%20the%20power%20to%20influence%20what%20buyers%20are%20willing%20to%20pay%20over%20the%20long%20term.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20growing%20national%20burden%20for%20buyers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EDaryl%20Fairweather%2C%20the%20chief%20economist%20at%20Redfin%2C%20said%20in%20an%20interview%20with%20Business%20Insider%20that%20rising%20insurance%20costs%20are%20especially%20severe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffalling-home-price-locations-us-housing-market-supply-florida-texas-2024-4%5C%22%3Ein%20states%20like%20Florida%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20climate%20disasters%20factor%20into%20the%20risk%20forecast%2C%20but%20they're%20rising%20all%20over%20the%20US.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20places%20all%20over%20the%20country%20that%20are%20gonna%20have%20their%20own%20climate%20issues%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20while%20referring%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftexas-heat-wave-weather-costs-economy-workers-jobs-2023-7%5C%22%3ETexas%20heat%20waves%20last%20summer%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20she%20said%20are%20likely%20to%20be%20repeated%20this%20year%2C%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwestern-us-wildfires-smoke-reached-east-coast-air-quality-2021-7%5C%22%3Epersistent%20smoke%20and%20wild%20fires%20plaguing%20the%20West%20Coast%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20insurance%20costs%20usually%20come%20as%20a%20surprise%20to%20home%20buyers%20in%20those%20areas%2C%20Fairweather%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20problem%20is%20that%20most%20people%20don't%20go%20through%20the%20process%20of%20finding%20out%20how%20much%20insurance%20will%20cost%20until%20they've%20already%20made%20an%20offer%20on%20a%20home%20and%20they%20feel%20like%20they%20have%20to%20go%20through%20with%20it%20or%20they'll%20lose%20out%20on%20their%20earnest%20money%20if%20they%20back%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EPressuring%20home%20prices%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EDanielle%20Hale%2C%20the%20chief%20economist%20at%20Realtor.com%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20lenders%20typically%20require%20various%20forms%20of%20insurance%20from%20buyers%20who%20take%20on%20a%20mortgage%2C%20and%20if%20the%20insurance%20costs%20are%20too%20high%2C%20it%20can%20disqualify%20the%20buyer%20from%20getting%20the%20loan.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20costs%20rise%2C%20the%20pool%20of%20buyers%20who%20can%20qualify%20for%20the%20mortgage%20is%20more%20limited%2C%20and%20the%20price%20of%20the%20home%20may%20need%20to%20fall%20in%20order%20for%20a%20buyer%20to%20be%20found%2C%26quot%3B%20Hale%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJesse%20Keenan%2C%20a%20sustainable%20real%20estate%20and%20urban%20planning%20professor%20at%20Tulane%20University%2C%20said%20that%20homebuyers%20are%20very%20sensitive%20to%20the%20long-term%20operational%20costs%20of%20having%20insurance%2C%20and%20usually%2C%20the%20value%20of%20a%20home%20will%20decline%20if%20insurance%20is%20particularly%20costly.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20it's%20buyers%20and%20sellers%20capitalizing%20risk%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20they're%20coming%20to%20terms%20with%20what%20that%20risk%20may%20be.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20noted%20that%20insurance%20markets%20are%20getting%20better%20at%20discovering%20and%20assessing%20risk%2C%20thanks%20to%20things%20like%20geospatial%20technologies%20and%20advanced%20computing.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20implications%20of%20that%20are%20that%20technology%20is%20helping%20companies%20price%20at%20a%20much%20more%20precise%20measure%20of%20risk%2C%20so%20with%20all%20that%20information%2C%20consumers%20are%20now%20saying%2C%20'you%20know%20what%2C%20this%20is%20worth%20more%2C%20this%20is%20worth%20less.'%20And%20as%20a%20consequence%2C%20the%20value%20of%20propert