80%94%20by%20making%20expensive%20mistakes.%20But%20the%20best%20money%20lessons%20and%20habits%20I%20learned%20from%20my%20late%20husband.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20met%20Remi%20when%20I%20was%20in%20my%20second%20year%20at%20university%20in%20Montreal.%20I'd%20already%20made%20a%20few%20money%20blunders%20in%20the%20short%20time%20I'd%20been%20living%20on%20my%20own.%20Remi%20was%20six%20years%20older%20than%20me%2C%20a%20Ph.D.%20student%20at%20the%20time.%20A%20little%20over%20a%20year%20after%20we%20met%2C%20we%20moved%20to%20Switzerland%20together%20for%20Remi's%20work.%20Romantic%2C%20yes.%20Expensive%2C%20YOU%20BET!%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20I%20didn't%20have%20a%20visa%20to%20stay%20in%20Switzerland%2C%20which%20meant%20I%20couldn't%20work%20there%20and%20had%20to%20make%20several%20trips%20back%20to%20Canada%20every%20year.%20That's%20when%20I%20started%20accumulating%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-credit-cards%5C%22%3Ecredit%20card%3C%2Fa%3E%20debt%20that%20would%20take%20me%20years%20to%20pay%20off.%20Over%20the%2011%20beautiful%20years%20Remi%20and%20I%20spent%20together%20before%20his%20sudden%2C%20tragic%20death%2C%20Remi%20helped%20me%20develop%20good%20money%20habits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Remi's%20absence%2C%20I've%20slowly%20assembled%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmeet-with-financial-experts-every-january-2024-1%5C%22%3Ea%20team%20of%20financial%20experts%3C%2Fa%3E%20I%20trust%20to%20help%20me%20manage%20my%20money%20as%20I%20build%20my%20own%20financial%20literacy%20without%20him%2C%20but%20I'm%20also%20relying%20on%20everything%20I%20learned%20with%20him.%20Here%20are%20the%20best%20money%20lessons%20I%20learned%20from%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20Pay%20off%20your%20credit%20card%20debt%20to%20%240%20every%20month.%20No%20skipsies.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20may%20seem%20obvious%2C%20but%20not%20all%20of%20us%20are%20doing%20it.%20In%202013%2C%20I%20finally%20paid%20off%20years%20of%20credit%20debt%2C%20and%20I've%20never%20looked%20back.%20For%20years%20I%20only%20made%20the%20minimum%20payments%2C%20barely%20making%20a%20dent%20in%20my%20debt.%20Once%20I%20was%20legally%20able%20to%20work%20in%20Switzerland%2C%20Remi%20and%20I%20worked%20together%20to%20create%20a%20payment%20plan%20that%20involved%20putting%20nearly%20all%20of%20my%20earnings%20directly%20toward%20paying%20off%20my%20credit%20card%20debt%20until%20it%20was%20down%20to%20%240.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20only%20possible%20because%20Remi%20was%20able%20to%20support%20us%20financially%20during%20that%20time%2C%20while%20I%20took%20on%20all%20household%20duties.%20Of%20course%2C%20the%20bulk%20of%20my%20debt%20was%20from%20plane%20tickets%20that%20I%20wouldn't%20have%20purchased%20had%20we%20not%20been%20living%20abroad%20and%20in%20a%20place%20where%20I%20couldn't%20legally%20work%20at%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat's%20important%20here%20is%20that%20we%20both%20agreed%20to%20the%20situation%2C%20understanding%20that%20it%20was%20only%20temporary.%20In%20hindsight%2C%20there%20were%20other%20options%20available%20to%20help%20us%20through%20this%20difficult%20financial%20time%2C%20including%20transferring%20my%20credit%20card%20debt%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fpersonal-loan-vs-line-of-credit%5C%22%3Eline%20of%20credit%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20a%20more%20manageable%20interest%20rate%2C%20for%20example.%20But%20the%20lesson%20was%20loud%20and%20clear%20to%20me%3A%20Don't%20carry%20credit%20card%20debt.%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20Out%20of%20sight%20is%20far%20from%20out%20of%20mind%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20meeting%20Remi%2C%20I%20didn't%20have%20a%20budget.%20I%20worried%20about%20money%20all%20the%20time%2C%20but%20I%20rarely%20looked%20at%20my%20finances.%20I%20had%20a%20seriously%20avoidant%20attachment%20style%20when%20it%20came%20to%20my%20money.%20I%20was