%5C%22%3Ecognitive%20behavioral%20therapy%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThroughout%20her%20studies%2C%20she%20grew%20angrier%20at%20how%20sociopaths%20are%20portrayed%20in%20the%20media%20and%20not%20prioritized%20in%20mental%20health%20spaces.%20%26quot%3BThese%20were%20human%20beings%20deserving%20of%20serious%20clinical%20attention%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BInstead%2C%20they%20were%20treated%20with%20malevolence%20and%20exiled.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGagne%20said%20her%20personal%20experience%20and%20ability%20to%20remain%20emotionally%20detached%20made%20her%20uniquely%20qualified%20to%20help%20otherwise%20maligned%20patients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EShe%20took%20on%20patients%20no%20one%20else%20wanted%20to%20treat%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20get%20her%20PhD%2C%20Gagne%20had%20to%20log%20500%20hours%20as%20a%20clinic%20intern%20%E2%80%94%20something%20she%20objected%20to%2C%20at%20first%2C%20because%20she%20was%20worried%20her%20sociopathy%20would%20make%20her%20a%20bad%20therapist.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGagne%20said%20she%20often%20got%20patients%20%26quot%3Bwho%20didn't%20fit%20neatly%20into%20any%20diagnostic%20box.%26quot%3B%20They%20had%20personality%20traits%20she%20recognized%20in%20herself%2C%20such%20as%20a%20feeling%20of%20emptiness%2C%20a%20history%20of%20criminal%20and%20violent%20behavior%2C%20and%20difficulty%20with%20impulse%20control.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20she%20was%20licensed%2C%20she%20said%20she%20%26quot%3Bearned%20a%20low-key%20reputation%20as%20'the%20sociopath%20therapist%2C'%26quot%3B%20and%20took%20on%20similar%20patients%20that%20her%20cohorts%20felt%20unable%20to%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20practice%20was%20like%20a%20psychology%20speakeasy%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BUnlicensed%20and%20unorthodox%2C%20I%20welcomed%20the%20misfits%20nobody%20else%20wanted%20to%20see.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EShe%20observed%20clients%20without%20her%20emotions%20getting%20in%20the%20way%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20book%2C%20Gagne%20wrote%20about%20a%20time%20when%20the%20head%20of%20her%20PhD%20department%20told%20her%20that%20her%20sociopathy%20might%20actually%20come%20in%20handy%20when%20dealing%20with%20patients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B'Half%20the%20battle%20in%20clinical%20training%20is%20helping%20trainees%20compartmentalize%20their%20own%20emotional%20attachments%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20to%20Gagne%20before%20she%20started%20her%20internship.%20%26quot%3B'But%20you%20don't%20have%20any!'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20she%20acclimated%20to%20her%20role%20at%20the%20clinic%2C%20she%20realized%20that%20being%20a%20sociopath%20came%20with%20strengths.%20%26quot%3BWith%20my%20patients%2C%20there's%20no%20expectation%20for%20me%20to%20feel%20or%20relate%20or%20connect%20or%20even%20talk%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20to%20her%20dad.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20have%20to%20do%20anything%20but%20observe.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20she%20could%20take%20on%20a%20more%20detached%20role%2C%20she%20also%20was%20able%20to%20better%20understand%20other%20sociopaths%20with%20time.%20Even%20though%20empathy%20is%20one%20of%20the%20emotions%20sociopaths%20can't%20reach%2C%20Gagne%20said%20she%20was%20%26quot%3Bflooded%20with%20understanding%26quot%3B%20as%20she%20met%20more%20and%20more%20patients%20like%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EShe'd%20bend%20the%20rules%20if%20it%20helped%20someone%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20her%20time%20at%20the%20clinic%2C%20Gagne%20had%20a%20patient%20who%20canceled%20an%20appointment%20%E2%80%94%20something%20that%20was%20out%20of%20character%20for%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGagne%20called%20her%2C%20and%20she%20said%20she%20was%20at%20home.%20Gagne%20asked%20for%20a%20photo%20of%20her%20living%20room.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20request%20was%20highly%20unorthodox%2C%26quot%3B%20Gagne%20says%20in%20the%20book.%20%26quot%3BAsking%20a%20patient%20to%20send%20me%20proof%20of%20their%20physical%20