track.io%2Flink%2F22c1af7d529d2ac4059ccfbae59dda9a0b6b6aa7%3Furl%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Fwww.steviehowell.com%252F%26userId%3D2243642%26signature%3D600fbe5c00dbb74c%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EStevie%20Howell%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20an%20artist%20and%20business%20owner%20who%20lives%20in%20Los%20Angeles.%20It's%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20born%20and%20raised%20in%20San%20Francisco%20and%20lived%20there%20for%20six%20years%20of%20my%20adult%20life%20before%20moving%C2%A0to%20Los%20Angeles%20about%20five%20years%20ago.%20I%20thought%20it%20would%20be%20a%20very%20easy%20move%2C%20but%20I've%20been%20surprised%20by%20some%20things%20that%20a%20huge%20city%20like%20LA%C2%A0doesn't%C2%A0have%20compared%20to%20tiny%20SF.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20love%20to%20hate%20San%20Francisco%20%E2%80%94%20I%20heard%20the%20word%20%26quot%3Bwar-torn%26quot%3B%20used%20to%20describe%20it%20just%20the%20other%20day%20%E2%80%94%20but%20the%20truth%20is%20it's%20gorgeous.%20The%20city%20has%20parks%20and%20incredible%20views%2C%20and%20the%20hills%20are%20picturesque%20and%20fun%20to%20drive%20up%20and%20down.%20There's%20great%20architecture%20%E2%80%94%20from%20colorful%20Victorians%20to%20the%C2%A0monstrous%20Salesforce%20tower%20%E2%80%94%20and%20easy%20access%20to%20the%20ocean%20and%20the%20Bay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20well-planned%20urban%20space%2C%20and%20the%20city%20continues%20to%20make%20thoughtful%20decisions%20in%20terms%20of%20keeping%20it%20visually%20stunning%20and%20stimulating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20LA%20is%20much%20larger%20than%20San%20Francisco%2C%20LA%C2%A0doesn't%C2%A0feel%20urban%2C%20while%20San%20Francisco%20does.%20Here's%20what%20I%20felt%20were%20the%20five%20worst%20things%20about%20leaving%20the%20San%20Francisco%20Bay%20Area%20and%20moving%20to%20LA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20LA%20feels%20socially%20distant%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELA%20feels%20like%20a%20vast%20network%20of%20suburban%20enclaves.%20I%20get%20an%20urban%20buzz%20in%20San%20Francisco%20%E2%80%94%20that%20hum%20of%20activity%20and%20people%20moving%20around%20rather%20than%20staying%20in%20their%20houses%20like%20they%20do%20in%20LA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESan%20Francisco%20is%20relatively%20condensed%2C%20so%20you%20know%20your%20neighbors%2C%20can%20walk%20to%20get%20coffee%20or%20go%20grocery%20shopping%2C%20meet%20up%20with%20a%20friend%20last%20minute%2C%20or%20go%20to%20dinner%20crosstown%20and%20not%20spend%20your%20entire%20evening%20trying%20to%20get%20there%20as%20we%20do%20in%20LA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20I%20miss%20the%20diverse%20food%2C%20art%2C%20and%20neighborhoods%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWalking%20around%2C%20you%20can%20hear%20a%20mixture%20of%20languages%20and%20eat%20a%20range%20of%20cuisines.%20There's%20amazing%20food%20and%20so%20many%20creative%20chefs%20doing%20great%20things.%20A%20few%20restaurants%20that%20I%20miss%20most%20are%20Flour%20%2B%20Water%20(Italian)%2C%20Mandalay%20SF%20(Burmese%20food)%2C%20Marnee%20Thai%20(Thai)%2C%20La%20Taqueria%20(Mexican)%2C%20and%20Swan%20Oyster%20Depot%20(seafood).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20heard%20the%20art%20world%20in%20San%20Francisco%20referred%20to%20as%20%26quot%3Bprovincial%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20it's%20home%20to%20both%20amazing%20galleries%20and%20important%20collections.%20Some%20of%20my%20favorites%20are%20Jessica%20Silverman%20Gallery%2C%20SFMOMA%2C%20Rebecca%C2%A0Camacho%C2%A0Presents%2C%20and%20Minnesota%20Street%20Project.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20each%20neighborhood%20has%20its%20own%20identity%2C%20personality%2C%20and%20unique%20characters.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20I%20miss%20San%20Francisco's%20support%20system%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20loved%20the%20community%20I%20had%20at%20my%20studio%3B%20it's%20a%20sense%20of%20community%20that%20I%20haven't%20found%20in%20any%20other%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20art%20studio%20was%20at%20the%20end%20of%20an%20old%20wooden%20building%20among%20a%20bunch%20of%20beautiful%20old%20brick%20warehouses%20and%20ship-building%20facilities.%20Other%20artists%20lived%20in%20the%20building%2C%20and%20we%20helped%20each%20other%20out.%20We%20referred%20new%20clients%20to%20each%20other%2C%20pitched%20each%20other's%20work%20to%20the%20press%2C%20and%20shared%20resources%20for%20opportunities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20an%20artist%20and%20business%20owner%2C%20I%20founded%20my%20eco-friendly%20textile%20and%20wallpaper%20collection%20business%20in%20San%20Francisco%20in%202013.%20I%C2%A0don't%C2%A0think%20I%20ever%20would've%20started%20a%20business%20in%20another%20city.%20San%20Francisco%20breeds%20entrepreneurship%20that%20goes%20beyond%20the%20tech%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20I%20miss%20San%20Francisco's%20culture%20and%20philanthropic%20spirit%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELiving%20in%20San%20Francisco%2C%20I%20found%20that%20many%20of%20its%20businesses%20have%20a%20good%20environmental%20or%20social%20mission.%20I%20miss%20the%20philanthropy%20that's%20woven%20into%20the%20city.%20People%20care%20about%20the%20world%20and%20each%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20San%20Francisco%20has%20gotten%20many%20things%20right%2C%20the%20way%20it%20deals%20with%20%E2%80%94%20or%20doesn't%20deal%20with%20%E2%80%94%20the%20homeless%20crisis%20is%20one%20thing%20it's%20gotten%20wrong.%20It%20stems%20from%20how%20the%20city%20deals%20with%20drug%20addiction%2C%20mental%20illness%2C%20and%20its%20high%20cost%20of%20living.%20Many%20other%20cities%20in%20the%20US%20are%20facing%20similar%20issues%2C%20and%20like%20other%20cities%2C%20it's%20upsetting%20to%20see.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20I%20believe%2C%20for%20the%20most%20part%2C%20San%20Francisco%20still%20has%20the%20same%20caring%20heart%20and%20soul%20it's%20had%20for%20years.%C2%A0People%20care%20about%20their%20neighbors%2C%20their%20parks%2C%20and%20the%20greater%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20I%20miss%20the%20Bay%20Area's%20accessibility%20to%20the%20outdoors%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20so%20much%20amazing%20green%20space%20and%20beach%20around%20the%20Bay%20Area%20that's%20easy%20to%20get%20to.%20You%20can%20take%20a%20hike%20on%20your%20lunch%20break.%20Crissy%20Field%2C%20Golden%20Gate%20Park%2C%20Bernal%20Heights%20Hill%2C%20Dolores%20Park%2C%20Ocean%20Beach%2C%20Stinson%20Beach%2C%20Angel%20Island%2C%20and%20Rodeo%20Beach%20are%20great%20spots.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20lived%20in%20San%20Francisco%2C%20I%20was%20on%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.parksconservancy.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGolden%20Gate%20National%20Parks%20Conservancy%3C%2Fa%3E%20committee%20and%20got%20to%20learn%20in-depth%20about%20how%20much%20thought%20goes%20into%20each%20individual%20plant%20that's%20planted%20in%20the%20city%2C%20and%20the%20education%20and%20research%20that's%20happening%20in%20the%20city's%20parks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20access%20to%20the%20outdoors%20and%20natural%20beauty%20is%20also%20what%20made%20the%20Bay%20Area%20such%20an%20incredible%20place%20to%20grow%20up.%20There's%20truly%20a%20mix%20of%20indoor%20and%20outdoor%20learning%20that's%20incomparable%20to%20LA%20or%20anywhere%20else%20I've%20lived.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIf%20you%20moved%20to%20a%20new%20city%20or%20state%20and%20want%20to%20share%20your%20experience%2C%20email%20Manseen%20Logan%20at%20mlogan%40businessinsider.com.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-worst-things-about-leaving-san-francisco-for-la-2024-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1714821062000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F661ecba310c6b0cde5f013de%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-worst-things-about-leaving-san-francisco-for-la-2024-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22This